Ashley Nicolette Frangipane -LRB- born September 29 , 1994 -RRB- , known professionally as Halsey -LRB- -LSB- ` hɔːl.zi -RSB- -RRB- , is an American singer and songwriter .
In 2014 , she signed her first recording contract with Astralwerks and released her debut EP , titled Room 93 .
Her debut studio album , Badlands , was released in 2015 .
Her professional name , Halsey , is a reference to the Halsey Street station of the New York City Subway in Brooklyn as well as an anagram of her first name , Ashley .